# Library App — Agent Context

**Always read these files first** when starting work on this project:

1. [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) — Main agent guide, architecture, constraints
2. [.ai/README.md](.ai/README.md) — Agent skills, workflows, slash commands (single source of truth)

**Before any task or feature**: Pull `main` and resolve merge conflicts — `git fetch origin main && git merge origin/main` — then proceed.

Slash commands: `/run-tests`, `/logs`, `/build`, `/migrate`, `/db-shell` (see `.ai/commands/` for details).

**Skills** (see [.ai/skills/](.ai/skills/) for details): create-pr, unit-test-runner, integration-test-runner — spec-exec uses test runners when running tests; do not trust Failsafe exit code alone.

**Task agents** (see [.ai/agents/](.ai/agents/) for details): task-spec — use when asked to draft a task spec; task-exec — use when asked to implement or verify a task.
